# Frontend

- is inside a bun monorepo
- the frontend folder is /apps/next
- uses NextJs version 14
- uses shadcn for frontend components

## Principles (Next 14 server-first)
- default to Server Components (RSC); use `use client` only when interaction/state is needed
- avoid Next API routes; prefer backend in apps/api and call via fetch
- colocate small UI logic with components; move business logic to use-cases in packages

## Structure and Naming
- app/: routing, layouts, error.tsx, loading.tsx
- components/: UI components; shadcn components under components/ui
- lib/: small frontend utilities (formatting, adapters for fetch)
- components and files: PascalCase for components; use *.client.tsx only when it helps clarity

## Data Fetching and Caching
- fetch in Server Components by default
- use revalidate for ISR or noStore() for dynamic data
- use Suspense/streaming for heavy lists (e.g., event-list) and skeletons for perceived performance
- avoid global singleton clients in the browser; send serialized data from server

## State and Forms
- keep local state minimal in Client Components
- prefer Server Actions when viable; otherwise call apps/api via fetch with typed DTOs
- handle optimistic updates carefully; reconcile with server responses

## Performance
- use next/image; avoid dangerouslySetInnerHTML unless sanitized
- split large components; memoize selectively for stable props
- avoid unnecessary client hydration; promote server-first rendering

## Accessibility
- always provide alt text for images
- use appropriate ARIA roles and associate labels with inputs

## Cheat Sheet

### Server-first vs Client component
```tsx
// Server Component (default)
export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getData() // fetch on server
  return <List data={data} />
}

'use client'
export function InteractiveWidget() {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false)
  return <Button onClick={() => setOpen(!open)}>Toggle</Button>
}
```

### Data fetching with caching
```ts
export const revalidate = 300 // ISR 5 minutes
// or
import { unstable_noStore as noStore } from 'next/cache'
noStore()
```

### Suspense/streaming for heavy lists
```tsx
import { Suspense } from 'react'

export default function Page() {
  return (
    <Suspense fallback={<SkeletonRows quantity={10} />}> 
      <EventList />
    </Suspense>
  )
}
```

### Typed fetch to apps/api with DTOs
```ts
// packages/events/domain/dtos/event.dto.ts
export type EventDto = {
  id: string
  title: string
  startDate: string
}
```

```ts
// apps/next/lib/http.ts
export async function getJson<T>(input: RequestInfo, init?: RequestInit): Promise<T> {
  const res = await fetch(input, init)
  if (!res.ok) throw new Error('HTTP error ' + res.status)
  return await res.json()
}
```

```tsx
// apps/next/app/events/page.tsx (Server Component)
import type { EventDto } from '@events/domain/dtos'
import { getJson } from '@/lib/http'

export const revalidate = 300

export default async function EventsPage() {
  const events = await getJson<EventDto[]>(`${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL}/events`)
  return <EventList data={events} />
}
```

### Server Action: create event with validation
```tsx
// apps/next/app/events/new/page.tsx (Server Component)
import { revalidatePath } from 'next/cache'

export default function NewEventPage() {
  async function createEvent(formData: FormData) {
    'use server'
    const title = String(formData.get('title') || '')
    const startDate = String(formData.get('startDate') || '')
    if (!title || !startDate) return { success: false, reason: 'Missing fields' }

    const res = await fetch(`${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL}/events`, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'content-type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ title, startDate }),
      cache: 'no-store',
    })
    if (!res.ok) return { success: false, reason: 'API error ' + res.status }
    revalidatePath('/events')
    return { success: true }
  }

  return (
    <form action={createEvent} className="space-y-4">
      <input name="title" placeholder="Title" />
      <input name="startDate" type="datetime-local" />
      <button type="submit">Create</button>
    </form>
  )
}
```


